ISTE NIT Durgapur proudly announces IMS India @ims.india as our Knowledge Partner and sponsor of CIT 5.0

IMS Learning Resources is India’s first test preparation institute for the CAT and other management entrance examinations, with around 100 centres in 50 cities across India.

Visit them at: www.imsindia.com/

Also register for CIT 5.0 at: http://cit.istenitdgp.com/

#iste #imsindia #partnership

ISTE unravels in front of you, one of the most precious and glorious events of the year, CIT 5.0, or the Cognitive Intelligence Test 5.0 . It's an exquisite journey into the vast unbound ocean of a plethora of interesting and mind-boggling puzzles on the subjects like basic mathematical aptitude, verbal and logical reasoning, and data interpretation. One of the most concrete attributes of CIT is that it allows participants to experience the overall screening procedure of the hiring companies and implants in you the ideas of CAT and various other associated aptitude tests held all over the country. Over the years, this highly acclaimed event of ISTE NIT Durgapur has attracted thousands of aspiring students from various colleges all over India. 

Cash prize worth rupees 7500 awaits you! 

ROUND 1 (QUALIFIER ROUND)

Slot 1: Jan 18 (7:00 PM-7:45 PM)
Slot 2: Jan 19 (7:00 PM-7:45 PM)
Slot 3: Jan 20 (8:00 PM-8:45 PM)

ROUND 2 (FINAL ROUND)

Jan 22 (8:00 PM-8:45 PM)

Each slot consists of 30 questions that have to be answered within the stipulated time. Participants can sit for any one of the 3 slots provided according to their wish. For each correct answer, +4 marks will be awarded and there will be negative marking of -1 for each wrong answer. 
 
This event is open for students of all colleges but scholarships will be provided only to students of IITs, NITs and, all other tier 1 colleges.

Buckle up your shoes and put on your seatbelts to be a part of this exciting event not only to gain valuable experience but also to win amazing cash prizes and scholarships upto 60% across all programs from IMS INDIA.

Register here: 
http://cit.istenitdgp.com/ (check description)
and 
https://bit.ly/3njws1E

#iste #cit #cit5.0 #technology #technicalevent #puzzles #logicalreasoning #mathematicalaptitude #datainterpretation #CAT #verbalreasoning #event #imsindia

"In a day, when you don’t come across any problems you can be sure that you are traveling in a wrong path"

Every year 12th January is observed as the National Youth Day to commemorate the birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda. Born in a traditional Bengali family and following his inclination towards spirituality, he became an epitome of convergence of modernization and ethics. An Indian Hindu monk and philosopher, Swami Vivekananda was a preeminent figure in introduction of the Indian darshanas of Vedanta and Yoga to the western world. His whole life is, and will always be the greatest motivation for the youths.

Remembering him today, our hearts at ISTE NIT Durgapur are filled with pride and an eternal positivity. "It’s all in the mind”, the theme for this year, suggests whether failure or success, every outcome depends on the mindset. Thoughts are permanent and "we become what we think about".

#swamivivekananda #12th #anniversary #celebration #iste #nit #durgapur

“One of the basic rules of the universe is that nothing is perfect. Perfection simply doesn't exist..... Without imperfection, neither you nor I would exist”

Arguably one of the greatest physicists of our time and a man whose theories changed the way the world looked at the cosmos, Stephen Hawking, someone whose work influenced the world of science like no other, was born in Oxfordshire, England on January 8, 1942.Even after being diagnosed with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) and despite his deteriorating physical condition, Hawking's unquenchable determination made him pursue his work. All his phenomenal works in the field of Black holes, origin of the universe, quantum mechanics and string theory still remain an epitome of modern theoretical physics.

The world of science was not the only one where Hawking had an impact. The movie "The Theory of Everything", named after one of his revolutionary books, was revered all over the world as one of the best biographic films ever made.

We here at ISTE NIT Durgapur, bow in respect and devotion to the doyen of modern theoretical physics and cherish the glimpses of his undying revelations.

#iste #stephenhawking #physics #theoryofeverything #physicist #8thjan #birthanniversary #blackhole #quantammechanics #space #universe

“No great discovery was ever made without a bold guess”

Sir Isaac Newton, a name so renowned that he needs no introduction, a pillar of modern science, a golden chapter in the history of inventions, whose laws shape our comprehension. Born on January 4, 1643, Sir Isaac Newton was an English physicist and mathematician, and a culminating figure of the Scientific Revolution of the 17th century. An epitome of intellect, the versatility of his contribution remains peerless. From Calculus to Optics, from Law of Gravity to the Laws of motion, numerous fields mark his presence. 

Remembering him today and his contributions, we here at ISTE NIT Durgapur are truly grateful to him for bringing in the light and making this world more understandable.

#iste #isaacnewton #physics #physicist #gravity #calculus #optics #motion #science #newton

"Time.... It flies... It waits for none..."

In this vast and weary world it leaves a man bewildered in its intricate fabric of mysteries... a boat that takes you forward through the river of memories... 

Leaving behind all the heartwarming and heartwrenching memorabilia of the previous year, we look forward to days of hope sprouting new beginnings. Together we welcome the panaroma of intriguing possibilities that lay ahead, to this unending journey across the horizon of the grand design of life. With great pomp and zeal we accomodate ourselves with new promises, believes, virtues and resolutions in order to stay firm in our path and strong in our minds. Even in these dark times, holding our heads high no matter what is in store, we all hope for a pleasant and memorable new year ahead. 

With a heavy heart filled with conflicting emotions, bidding a solemn farewell to the year that's gone by, we here at ISTE NIT DURGAPUR, wish everyone of you a safe, healthy, happy and prosperous new year 2022.

#newyear #newyear2022 #iste #happynewyear #2022 #happiness #celebration

ISTE magnanimously extends its support to BMEP, and invites everyone to be a part of their Annual Fundraiser 2021-2022. The pandemic ravaged for nearly the past two years and deterred the day to day life of people. Although, people with suitable amenities were able to cope up with it, young unprivileged kids were completely thrown into shadows in these dark times.

As we all know BMEP's motives and initiatives has always been helping children time and again. We here at ISTE NIT Durgapur always try to lay down a helping hand towards BMEP's noble goal to the best of our abilities. During the pre-covid era we had conducted "SCIJECT", an event that really had a significant impact on the children.

As a non-profit organization BMEP lacks a constant funding source, thus depending on its contributors. We humbly request your minimal contribution in making the lives of these underprivileged children better. Notwithstanding how much you contribute, your benevolent support in order to bring smile on their faces is what matters.

PLEASE DONATE HERE-
https://milaap.org/fundraisers/support-children-286?deeplink_type=upi&utm_medium=whatsapp_status&utm_source=app

PLEASE READ MORE-
https://milaap.org/fundraisers/support-children-286?utm_medium=whatsapp_status&utm_source=app

Milaap Impact partner will match 5% of your gracious donation for our fundraiser.

"One can never have enough socks," said Dumbledore. "Another Christmas has come and gone and I didn't get a single pair. People will insist on giving me books."

The merry vibes of Christmas is no better portrayed than in the movie "Tim Burton's The Nightmare Before Christmas" where Jack Skellington, a being from Halloween Town, finds Christmas Town and is instantly enchanted. He describes Christmas Town as a place of happiness, where he gets good vibes being among all those lights, and most importantly, doesn't feel empty. That's how humans feel today. Commemorating the birthday of Jesus Christ, people all over the world celebrate this day singing carols, decorating houses with fairy lights, baking Gingerbread cakes, roasting turkey and vibing to the happy spirits of Christmas. 

ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes all of you a Merry Christmas as we are looking forward to happiness in our lives.

#iste #christmas #jesus #merrychristmas #merrychristmas🎄 #happiness #birthday #birthofchrist #christmascake #festivevibes #chistmas2021 #25thdec

Greetings Freshers!

ISTE NIT Durgapur Chapter enthusiastically welcomes you all and extends its heartiest congratulations for making it this far and joining our prestigious institution of NIT Durgapur.

The Indian Society for Technical Education (ISTE) is a preeminent National Professional non-profit making Society for the Technical Education Structure in our country.

We are acclaimed for organizing unrivalled events around the year. From Cognitive Intelligence Test to Data Analytics Workshop, from CTTC Winter Training to Industrial trip, we work hard to make sure that technical education blooms in our college and in our country.

We are glad to inform you that finally, the wait is over. We are here with the most awaited Fresher’s Orientation. So, buckle your seats up and get ready for a detailed comprehension of the working of our society. And don’t forget, your queries are our responsibility.

So, mark your calendars, note down your doubts and join us at the Fresher’s Orientation of ISTE NIT Durgapur Chapter.

DATE: 28th December 2021

TIME: 6 p.m.

LINK: https://meet.google.com/vie-kwrh-eww

See you all!

#iste #orientation #freshers #college #society #istenitdgp #technicaleducation #allindiasociety

India witnessed doomsday on 26 November, 2008 when ten terrorists from the Lashkar-e-Taiba, a terrorist organization based in Pakistan, carried out a series of coordinated terrorist attacks at several places of Mumbai. The LeT terrorists laid siege to some of the most prominent places like the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Terminus, the Oberoi Trident, the Taj Mahal Hotel, Leopold Cafe, Cama Hospital and the Nariman House Jewish community centre, and killed 166 people. However, in these times of need, not only the security force but also civilians worked bravely and risked their lives to save the fellow Mumbaikars from being killed. At the end of 4 days, 9 out of 10 terrorists were killed, but that came at the price of the lives of several security officers, like Major Sandeep Unnikrishnan, Police Commissioner Ashok Kamte, ATS chief Hemant Karkare, to name a few. These people didn't think about their lives thus, setting an example for the entire nation of how the spirit of a true fighter should be and that it is not defined by the uniform they wear. 

Today marks thirteen years of the 26/11 terror attacks in Mumbai. We at ISTE NIT Durgapur pay homage to the victims of 26/11 terror attack and pray for the well being of their families. 

#iste #26_11attack #mumbai #26november #tajmahalhotel #terroristattack #terrorattack #2008

"Even Kings and emperors with heaps of wealth and vast dominion cannot compare with an ant filled with the love of God."
 ------ Guru Nanak

Guru Nanak Jayanti , popularly known as Gurupurab , is the Sikh community's most important and sacred festival, which is observed all over the world. It marks the auspicious birth occasion of Guru Nanak Dev ji (the first Sikh guru and the founder of Sikhism) who played a significant role in leading numerous people away from superstition and hypocrisy and showed them the correct path to salvation with unbound magnanimity.

Gurdwaras are decked with flowers and lights to commemorate this auspicious day. The Akhand Paath of Guru Granth Sahib (holy book of the Sikhs) usually begins in the gurdwaras two days before Gurpurab. The Panj Payaras (five cherished Sikhs) with Nishan Sahib (Sikh Flag) lead the Nagar kirtan one day before the Gurpurab. Gatka teams perform Gatka (a Sikhism-related traditional martial art) and stage mock fights with their own conventiona weapons.On this auspicious occasion, gurdwaras host langars, where everyone is welcomed for a complete feast. People sit in rows to enjoy the langar and exchange Gurpurab greetings with one another.

On this auspicious and glorious day of pride and happiness for people in general and the Sikh community in particular, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone an ecstatic Guru Nanak Jayanti .

#guru #nanak #jayanti #iste #nitdurgapur #celebration

"The children of today will make the India of tomorrow. The way we bring them up will determine the future of the country." - Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru

This glorious day, every year fills our heart with love, compassion and benevolence for the millions of children of our nation. This day is commemorated each year on 14th November to pay tribute to our first Prime Minister, Pt. Jawaharlal Nehru , whose love for the children of our country was sans bound. 

Nehru Ji had a glorious vision for children and considered that children are the upcoming future creators of the nation. If we need to preserve our future, then it is the duty of all of us to build the future of these children in a better direction. In a glimpse of his love for children, our land began to remember his birthday as Children’s Day. The main purpose of this celebration is to make all the citizens of India aware of giving rights to children to get the education. It is their right to grow in the proper direction and hence a well-organized and wealthy nation can be developed, depending on the future of the children.Since Jawaharlal Nehru used to say that the property of any nation is not in its repository but in their schools, hence we should recognize our children as the wealth of the country and protect them and develop their future.

We here at ISTE NIT Durgapur, with due respect to one of the most inspiring personalities in the history of India, Pt. Jawaharlal Nehru, commemorate his 132nd birthday and wish every child of this nation a memorable Children's Day.

#iste #childrensday #childrensday2021 #jawaharlalnehru #children #132ndbirthanniversary #schoolchildren #futureofworld #celebration #studentteacher
